<strong>BIBLIOGRAPHY ENTRY</strong>
<br><br>
References to classical authors normally appear only in footnotes or in&#45;text citations. Include them in the bibliography only if a specific modern translation is important or if different translations are being used.
<br><br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<em>Title of Book</em>. Translated by Translator&#8217;s given name and surname. Place of publication:	Publisher, year of publication.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<em><span class="hover" title="Title of Book">Beowulf</span></em>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Translator&#8217;s name">Translated by Seamus Heaney</span>. 
	<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">London</span>: 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Faber</span>, 
	<span class="hover" title="year of publication">1999</span>.
</blockquote>
